messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- The NotificationsController defines two handler methods mapped to the same path value "/notifications/{notificationId}":

- There is no class-level @RequestMapping on NotificationsController that would add a prefix, so the full path is exactly "/notifications/{notificationId}" with the path parameter named notificationId as in the source.
- No other methods (GET, POST, PATCH, OPTIONS, TRACE, HEAD) are declared for this path in the provided code. Per your instructions, acceptance is determined from the code (explicit @RequestMapping entries), so only PUT and DELETE are considered acceptable.
